---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { forgeUrl, githubOrgUrl, profileUrl, roadmapUrl } from '../data/products';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About AgentKitProject, the open ecosystem for portable Agent Kits."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>AgentKitProject is building open tools for portable Agent Kits.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The project exists to make repeatable AI work easier to create, move, inspect, share, and
        automate. The open-source core and app foundation are centered on portable kit artifacts
        rather than a single locked-in destination.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href={githubOrgUrl}>View GitHub organization</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={forgeUrl}>Start with Forge</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={roadmapUrl}>View roadmap</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="container grid two">
      <article class="content-panel">
        <h2>Why Agent Kits?</h2>
        <p>
          Teams and individuals repeat the same AI workflows every day. Agent Kits package the
          instructions, inputs, guardrails, examples, and output expectations that make those
          workflows reusable.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="content-panel">
        <h2>Why an ecosystem?</h2>
        <p>
          Building a kit is only the first step. AgentKitProject separates the lifecycle into clear
          products: Profile for shared identity, Forge for creation and local runs, Market for
          distribution, and Auto for future execution.
        </p>
        <p><a href={profileUrl}>Open AgentKitProfile account</a></p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
